<div class="tab-content">

<!-- ═══════════════ TAB: OVERVIEW ═══════════════ -->
<div class="tab-pane fade show active" id="tabOverview">
    <div class="row g-3">
        <div class="col-md-6">
            <div class="card info-card trf shadow-sm">
                <div class="card-body">
                    <h5 class="card-title"><i class="bi bi-arrow-left-right me-2 section-icon text-success"></i>Transfer In Plan</h5>
                    <p class="card-text small text-muted">Store-level weekly plan that calculates how much stock each store needs transferred in from the DC to meet sales demand while maintaining optimal stock levels.</p>
                    <ul class="small mb-0">
                        <li>SP: <code>SP_GENERATE_TRF_IN_PLAN</code></li>
                        <li>Output Table: <code>TRF_IN_PLAN</code></li>
                        <li>Key Output: <strong>TRF_IN_STK_Q</strong> (Transfer In Quantity)</li>
                        <li>Granularity: Store + Category + Week</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-6">
            <div class="card info-card pp shadow-sm">
                <div class="card-body">
                    <h5 class="card-title"><i class="bi bi-bag-check me-2 section-icon text-purple"></i>Purchase Plan</h5>
                    <p class="card-text small text-muted">DC-level weekly plan that calculates purchase requirements based on aggregated transfer-out quantities, DC stock, and closing stock targets.</p>
                    <ul class="small mb-0">
                        <li>SP: <code>SP_GENERATE_PURCHASE_PLAN</code></li>
                        <li>Output Table: <code>PURCHASE_PLAN</code></li>
                        <li>Key Output: <strong>BGT_PUR_Q_INIT</strong> (Purchase Quantity)</li>
                        <li>Granularity: RDC + Category + Week</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-6">
            <div class="card info-card ref shadow-sm">
                <div class="card-body">
                    <h5 class="card-title"><i class="bi bi-table me-2 section-icon text-warning"></i>Reference Tables</h5>
                    <p class="card-text small text-muted">Input data tables that feed into both plans. Maintained via CRUD screens and Bulk Upload.</p>
                    <div class="row small">
                        <div class="col-6">
                            <ul class="ref-table-list mb-0">
                                <li>Week Calendar</li>
                                <li>Store Master</li>
                                <li>Bin Capacity</li>
                                <li>Sale Quantity</li>
                                <li>Display Qty</li>
                            </ul>
                        </div>
                        <div class="col-6">
                            <ul class="ref-table-list mb-0">
                                <li>Store Stock</li>
                                <li>DC Stock</li>
                                <li>Del Pending</li>
                                <li>GRT Contribution</li>
                                <li>Product Hierarchy</li>
                            </ul>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-6">
            <div class="card info-card shadow-sm" style="border-left-color:#e67e22;">
                <div class="card-body">
                    <h5 class="card-title"><i class="bi bi-layers me-2 section-icon" style="color:#e67e22;"></i>Sub-Level Plans <span class="badge badge-new ms-1">New</span></h5>
                    <p class="card-text small text-muted">Runs full TRF + PP algorithm per sub-level using level-specific stock, Sale&times;CONT%, Display&times;CONT%.</p>
                    <ul class="small mb-0">
                        <li><strong>Macro MVGR</strong> — ST_CD + MAJ_CAT + DISP_MVGR_MATRIX</li>
                        <li><strong>Size</strong> — ST_CD + MAJ_CAT + SZ</li>
                        <li><strong>Segment</strong> — ST_CD + MAJ_CAT + SEG</li>
                        <li><strong>Vendor</strong> — ST_CD + MAJ_CAT + M_VND_CD</li>
                        <li>Inputs: <code>SUB_ST_STK_*</code>, <code>SUB_DC_STK_*</code>, Contribution tables</li>
                        <li>Output: <code>SUB_LEVEL_TRF_PLAN</code>, <code>SUB_LEVEL_PP_PLAN</code></li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-6">
            <div class="card info-card shadow-sm">
                <div class="card-body">
                    <h5 class="card-title"><i class="bi bi-pie-chart me-2 section-icon" style="color:#e67e22;"></i>Contribution Tables <span class="badge badge-new ms-1">New</span></h5>
                    <p class="card-text small text-muted">Store + Category level contribution % for each sub-level dimension.</p>
                    <div class="row small">
                        <div class="col-6">
                            <ul class="ref-table-list mb-0">
                                <li>Macro MVGR Contribution</li>
                                <li>Size Contribution</li>
                            </ul>
                        </div>
                        <div class="col-6">
                            <ul class="ref-table-list mb-0">
                                <li>Segment Contribution</li>
                                <li>Vendor Contribution</li>
                            </ul>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-6">
            <div class="card info-card shadow-sm">
                <div class="card-body">
                    <h5 class="card-title"><i class="bi bi-diagram-3 me-2 section-icon"></i>Execution Flow</h5>
                    <p class="card-text small text-muted">How plans are generated end-to-end.</p>
                    <ol class="small mb-0">
                        <li>Upload reference data (Bulk Upload / CRUD)</li>
                        <li>Upload contribution data (MVGR, Size, Segment, Vendor)</li>
                        <li>Execute <strong>Transfer In Plan</strong> (store-level)</li>
                        <li>Execute <strong>Purchase Plan</strong> (DC-level, reads Transfer In output)</li>
                        <li>Upload sub-level stock (4 Store + 4 DC per level)</li>
                        <li>Execute <strong>Sub-Level Plans</strong> (full algorithm per level)</li>
                        <li>Review output, export CSV / Pivot CSV</li>
                        <li><code>SP_RUN_ALL_PLANS_V3</code> runs main plans in sequence for all stores</li>
                    </ol>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<!-- ═══════════════ TAB: SYSTEM FEATURES ═══════════════ -->
<div class="tab-pane fade" id="tabFeatures">

    <!-- Dashboard -->
    <div class="card shadow-sm mb-3">
        <div class="card-header"><h5 class="card-title mb-0"><i class="bi bi-speedometer2 me-2"></i>Dashboard (Operations Command Center)</h5></div>
        <div class="card-body small">
            <div class="row">
                <div class="col-md-6">
                    <h6 class="fw-bold">KPIs &amp; Alerts</h6>
                    <ul>
                        <li><strong>4 Alert Cards</strong>: Critical Short Stores, Excess Stores, DC Short (RDC x Cat), Zero Stock + Demand</li>
                        <li><strong>10 KPI Cards</strong>: Stores, Categories, RDCs, Transfer In Qty, Purchase Qty, DC Short, DC Excess, Transfer Out, PO Raised, Del Pending</li>
                        <li><strong>Sub-Level Status</strong>: Per-level TRF/PP row counts + last run timestamps</li>
                        <li><strong>Data Health</strong>: 14 reference table row counts with Ready/Empty status</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                <div class="col-md-6">
                    <h6 class="fw-bold">Charts &amp; Tables</h6>
                    <ul>
                        <li><strong>6 Charts</strong>: TRF by Category, Weekly Trend (TRF+Sale+ClStk), RDC Horizontal Bar, Short vs Excess, PP by Category, PP Weekly Trend</li>
                        <li><strong>RDC Inventory Health Table</strong>: DC Stock, TRF Out, Purchase, Short/Excess per RDC</li>
                        <li><strong>Top 10 Tables</strong>: Short Stores, Excess Stores, DC Short, DC Excess</li>
                        <li><strong>Risk Categories</strong>: Top categories by Company Short with CRITICAL/AT RISK rating</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="alert alert-info py-2 mb-0 mt-2"><i class="bi bi-info-circle me-1"></i><strong>Drill-Down Filters:</strong> RDC, Category, FY Week — all multi-select with search. Data cached for 60s per filter combination.</div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Bulk Upload -->
    <div class="card shadow-sm mb-3">
        <div class="card-header"><h5 class="card-title mb-0"><i class="bi bi-upload me-2"></i>Bulk Upload</h5></div>
        <div class="card-body small">
            <div class="row">
                <div class="col-md-6">
                    <h6 class="fw-bold">Capabilities</h6>
                    <ul>
                        <li><strong>22 Tables Supported</strong>: 10 Reference + 4 Contribution + 4 Sub Store Stock + 4 Sub DC Stock</li>
                        <li><strong>Multi-Sheet Excel</strong>: Reads ALL sheets from a single .xlsx file and merges rows</li>
                        <li><strong>Replace or Append</strong>: Replace mode truncates table before upload; Append adds to existing data</li>
                        <li><strong>Performance</strong>: Uses <code>SqlBulkCopy</code> — 20 lakh+ rows in seconds</li>
                        <li><strong>File Limit</strong>: Up to 500 MB per upload (Excel or CSV)</li>
                        <li><strong>Header Row</strong>: First row treated as column headers (auto-mapped)</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                <div class="col-md-6">
                    <h6 class="fw-bold">Additional Features</h6>
                    <ul>
                        <li><strong>Download Sample</strong>: Auto-generated Excel template with correct column names + 1 sample row per table</li>
                        <li><strong>Download Data</strong>: Export entire table as CSV for backup/audit</li>
                        <li><strong>Live Row Counts</strong>: Shows current row count per table before/after upload</li>
                        <li><strong>Column Validation</strong>: Validates uploaded columns match expected schema</li>
                    </ul>
                    <h6 class="fw-bold mt-3">Supported Tables</h6>
                    <div class="row">
                        <div class="col-6"><code class="small">WEEK_CALENDAR</code>, <code>MASTER_ST_MASTER</code>, <code>MASTER_BIN_CAPACITY</code>, <code>QTY_SALE_QTY</code>, <code>QTY_DISP_QTY</code>, <code>STORE_STOCK</code>, <code>DC_STOCK</code>, <code>DEL_PENDING</code>, <code>MASTER_GRT_CONTRIBUTION</code>, <code>MASTER_PRODUCT_HIERARCHY</code></div>
                        <div class="col-6"><code class="small">ST_MAJ_CAT_MACRO_MVGR_PLAN</code>, <code>ST_MAJ_CAT_SZ_PLAN</code>, <code>ST_MAJ_CAT_SEG_PLAN</code>, <code>ST_MAJ_CAT_VND_PLAN</code>, <code>SUB_ST_STK_MVGR/SZ/SEG/VND</code>, <code>SUB_DC_STK_MVGR/SZ/SEG/VND</code></div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Plan Execution -->
    <div class="card shadow-sm mb-3">
        <div class="card-header"><h5 class="card-title mb-0"><i class="bi bi-lightning me-2"></i>Plan Execution &amp; Background Jobs</h5></div>
        <div class="card-body small">
            <div class="table-responsive">
                <table class="table table-sm table-bordered mb-0">
                    <thead class="table-dark"><tr><th>Feature</th><th>Page</th><th>Stored Procedure</th><th>Mode</th><th>Description</th></tr></thead>
                    <tbody>
                        <tr><td class="fw-bold">Single Store TRF</td><td>Execute Plan</td><td><code>SP_GENERATE_TRF_IN_PLAN</code></td><td>Sync (Web)</td><td>Run TRF for 1 store + category subset. ~10s per store.</td></tr>
                        <tr><td class="fw-bold">Full Run (All Stores)</td><td>Execute Plan</td><td><code>SP_RUN_ALL_PLANS</code></td><td><span class="badge bg-primary">Background</span></td><td>Truncates TRF+PP, runs bulk for all 657 stores. ~1-2 min. Live progress polling.</td></tr>
                        <tr><td class="fw-bold">Purchase Plan</td><td>Purchase Plan</td><td><code>SP_GENERATE_PURCHASE_PLAN</code></td><td>Sync (Web)</td><td>Run PP for week range + optional RDC/MajCat filter.</td></tr>
                        <tr><td class="fw-bold">Sub-Level (Per Level)</td><td>Sub-Level Plans</td><td><code>SP_GENERATE_SUB_LEVEL_TRF</code> + <code>SP_GENERATE_SUB_LEVEL_PP</code></td><td>Sync (Web)</td><td>Run TRF+PP for selected levels. Form submit.</td></tr>
                        <tr><td class="fw-bold">Sub-Level Full Run</td><td>Sub-Level Plans</td><td>Same SPs &times; 4 levels</td><td><span class="badge bg-primary">Background</span></td><td>Runs all 4 levels (MVGR, SZ, SEG, VND) sequentially in background. Live progress with level tracking.</td></tr>
                    </tbody>
                </table>
            </div>
            <div class="alert alert-warning py-2 mt-2 mb-0"><i class="bi bi-exclamation-triangle me-1"></i><strong>Background Jobs:</strong> Run in a singleton service — you can navigate away and come back. Job status is polled every 5 seconds. Only one job per type can run at a time.</div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Data Export -->
    <div class="card shadow-sm mb-3">
        <div class="card-header"><h5 class="card-title mb-0"><i class="bi bi-download me-2"></i>Data Export (CSV &amp; Pivot)</h5></div>
        <div class="card-body small">
            <div class="table-responsive">
                <table class="table table-sm table-bordered mb-0">
                    <thead class="table-dark"><tr><th>Export Type</th><th>Available On</th><th>Format</th><th>Description</th></tr></thead>
                    <tbody>
                        <tr><td class="fw-bold">CSV Export</td><td>All output pages + all reference tables</td><td>Row-per-record</td><td>Standard flat CSV. Filters applied before export. Streamed for large datasets (13M+ rows).</td></tr>
                        <tr><td class="fw-bold">Pivot CSV</td><td>TRF Output, PP Output, Sub-Level TRF, Sub-Level PP</td><td>Weeks as columns</td><td>One row per entity (ST_CD+MAJ_CAT or RDC+MAJ_CAT+SUB_VALUE), metrics pivoted by week: <code>WK1_SALE, WK1_TRF_IN, WK2_SALE...</code></td></tr>
                        <tr><td class="fw-bold">Dashboard CSV</td><td>Dashboard</td><td>Full table dump</td><td>Export entire TRF_IN_PLAN or PURCHASE_PLAN from dashboard header.</td></tr>
                        <tr><td class="fw-bold">Bulk Download</td><td>Bulk Upload page</td><td>CSV</td><td>Download any reference table's full data as CSV for backup.</td></tr>
                    </tbody>
                </table>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Reset / Clear -->
    <div class="card shadow-sm mb-3">
        <div class="card-header"><h5 class="card-title mb-0"><i class="bi bi-trash me-2 text-danger"></i>Reset / Clear Data</h5></div>
        <div class="card-body small">
            <div class="table-responsive">
                <table class="table table-sm table-bordered mb-0">
                    <thead class="table-dark"><tr><th>Action</th><th>Page</th><th>SQL Operation</th><th>Scope</th></tr></thead>
                    <tbody>
                        <tr><td class="fw-bold text-danger">Reset Transfer In</td><td>Execute Plan</td><td><code>TRUNCATE TABLE TRF_IN_PLAN</code></td><td>All TRF rows deleted</td></tr>
                        <tr><td class="fw-bold text-danger">Reset Purchase Plan</td><td>Purchase Plan</td><td><code>TRUNCATE TABLE PURCHASE_PLAN</code></td><td>All PP rows deleted</td></tr>
                        <tr><td class="fw-bold text-danger">Reset Sub-Level (per level)</td><td>Sub-Level Plans</td><td><code>DELETE WHERE LEVEL='X'</code></td><td>Only selected level (MVGR/SZ/SEG/VND)</td></tr>
                        <tr><td class="fw-bold text-danger">Reset Sub-Level (all)</td><td>Sub-Level Plans</td><td><code>TRUNCATE TABLE SUB_LEVEL_TRF_PLAN + PP</code></td><td>All 4 levels deleted</td></tr>
                    </tbody>
                </table>
            </div>
            <div class="alert alert-danger py-2 mt-2 mb-0"><i class="bi bi-exclamation-triangle-fill me-1"></i>All reset actions require JavaScript confirmation. These are <strong>irreversible</strong> — data must be regenerated after reset.</div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- CRUD on Reference Tables -->
    <div class="card shadow-sm mb-3">
        <div class="card-header"><h5 class="card-title mb-0"><i class="bi bi-pencil-square me-2"></i>CRUD Operations (Reference Tables)</h5></div>
        <div class="card-body small">
            <p>Every reference and contribution table has a dedicated page under <strong>Reference Tables</strong> or <strong>Contribution</strong> in the sidebar with:</p>
            <div class="row">
                <div class="col-md-6">
                    <ul>
                        <li><strong>Index</strong>: Searchable/sortable DataTable with filters, pagination, row counts</li>
                        <li><strong>Create</strong>: Add a single row via form</li>
                        <li><strong>Edit</strong>: Modify an existing row</li>
                        <li><strong>Delete</strong>: Remove a single row with confirmation</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                <div class="col-md-6">
                    <ul>
                        <li><strong>Export CSV</strong>: Download filtered data as CSV</li>
                        <li><strong>Analytics Cards</strong>: Total Rows + 2-3 table-specific KPIs (avg, distinct counts, etc.)</li>
                        <li><strong>Search Dropdowns</strong>: Searchable filter dropdowns for key columns</li>
                        <li><strong>10 Reference + 4 Contribution + 8 Sub-Stock = 22 table pages</strong></li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Technology Stack -->
    <div class="card shadow-sm">
        <div class="card-header"><h5 class="card-title mb-0"><i class="bi bi-stack me-2"></i>Technology Stack</h5></div>
        <div class="card-body small">
            <div class="row">
                <div class="col-md-4">
                    <h6 class="fw-bold">Backend</h6>
                    <ul class="mb-0">
                        <li>ASP.NET Core 8.0 MVC</li>
                        <li>Entity Framework Core (SQL Server)</li>
                        <li>Raw SQL + SqlBulkCopy for performance</li>
                        <li>IMemoryCache (60s dashboard cache)</li>
