                </table>
            </div>
            <div class="alert alert-info py-2 mb-0 small border-0 rounded-0">
                <i class="bi bi-info-circle me-1"></i><strong>Key:</strong> Reads TRF_OUT from SUB_LEVEL_TRF_PLAN (must run TRF first). DC stock from <code>SUB_DC_STK_{MVGR|SZ|SEG|VND}</code>. Full DC chain algorithm per SUB_VALUE.
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="card shadow-sm">
        <div class="card-header"><h5 class="card-title mb-0"><i class="bi bi-diagram-2 me-2"></i>Execution Flow</h5></div>
        <div class="card-body small">
            <ol>
                <li><strong>Upload Contribution Data</strong> — 4 Excel files (MVGR, Size, Segment, Vendor) via Bulk Upload. Each has ST_CD, MAJ_CAT_CD, sub-value, CONT_PCT.</li>
                <li><strong>Upload Sub-Level Stock</strong> — 4 Store Stock tables (<code>SUB_ST_STK_*</code>) + 4 DC Stock tables (<code>SUB_DC_STK_*</code>) via Bulk Upload.</li>
                <li><strong>Ensure Main Reference Data Exists</strong> — Sale Qty, Display Qty, Bin Capacity, Store Master, Week Calendar must be populated.</li>
                <li><strong>Generate Sub-Level Plans</strong> — Go to Sub-Level Plans page, select week range, optional MajCat/StoreCode filters, select levels, click Generate.</li>
                <li><strong>Algorithm Runs Per Level</strong> — TRF SP runs first (full chain with level-specific stock), then PP SP reads from TRF output.</li>
                <li><strong>View Output</strong> — TRF Output and PP Output per level with filters, pagination, CSV export.</li>
            </ol>
            <div class="alert alert-warning py-2 mb-0"><i class="bi bi-exclamation-triangle me-1"></i><strong>Important:</strong> Sub-Level plans run the <strong>full algorithm independently</strong> — they are NOT derived from main plan output. Main plan execution is NOT required first.</div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

